description: {"blocks":[{"key":"c5fp2","text":"As a product of anaerobic glycolysis L-lactate has shown to be an important indicator of the cellular metabolic status and can be associated with diverse cellular effects. For this reason, L-lactate assay kits are in high demand when metabolic effects need to be examined. Nevertheless, commercially available kits are not affordable if multiple samples must be evaluated. This protocol uses LDH activity to determine the concentration of L-lactate as a product of metabolism in cellular supernatant and is suitable for 96 well-plate format. The protocol provides repeatable results and exhibits an easy and cost-effective alternative for any lab with a microplate absorbance reader capable of measuring millimolar amount of L-lactate in supernatant.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5v43","text":"Add 50 μL of RPMI medium or the medium used for cell culture to the appropriate wells of a flat-bottom 96-well plate as Blank. (See Table 1 as template). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e1079","text":"Test all the samples, controls and standards with a minimum of two replicates. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5qsea","text":"For the standard curve, add 50 μL of L-lactate Standards to the appropriate wells of the flat-bottom 96-well plate (Table 1). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5pr51","text":"For samples, add 50 μL of sample (e.g. supernatant) to the appropriate wells of the flat-bottom 96-well plate (Table 1). (Cell supernatant can be stored in an unsterile 96-well plate at -20°C if it is necessary). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f73ar","text":"It is possible to dilute the samples with medium in case the samples present higher concentrations of L-lactate than the standard curve. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3pt35","text":"Add 50 μL of Assay Buffer to the wells.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6ijg5","text":"Incubate for 1h at room temperature in the dark. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8n9mh","text":"Add 50 μL of Acetic Acid 1 mol/L to stop the reaction (any bubbles produced by pipetting need to be removed for an exact measurement).","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"10esk","text":"Read the absorbance at 490 nm-Ref 650 nm with a microplate absorbance reader.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ksq7","text":"Subtract the blank from all data points, including standads and samples and then use a curve-fitting sofware to create the standard curve.
